### Customer API Requests
# This file contains HTTP requests for testing Customer endpoints.
# You can use the REST Client extension in VS Code to run these.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@authToken = YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE
@customerId = 1

### 1. Get All Customers
# Returns a list of all customers with their order history.
GET {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

# Expected Response: 200 OK
# {
#   "status": "success",
#   "message": "Customers fetched successfully",
#   "data": [...]
# }


### 2. Get Single Customer
# Returns detailed information about a specific customer including orders and refunds.
GET {{baseUrl}}/customers/{{customerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

# Expected Response: 200 OK / 404 Not Found


### 3. Create Customer
# Creates a new customer record. Supports combined 'name' field.
POST {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "phone": "+1234567890",
    "address": "123 Main St, Anytown, USA",
    "businessName": "John's Store",
    "customerType": "retail"
}

# Expected Response: 201 Created


### 4. Update Customer
# Updates an existing customer record.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/customers/{{customerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "name": "John Updated",
    "email": "john.updated@example.com",
    "phone": "+1987654321",
    "address": "456 Side St, Othertown, USA",
    "businessName": "John's New Store",
    "customerType": "retail"
}

# Expected Response: 200 OK


### 5. Delete Customer
# Deletes a customer. Only allowed if they have no active orders.
# Requires CEO or Manager role.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/customers/{{customerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

# Expected Response: 200 OK / 400 Bad Request (if has orders)
